  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Esther Sturge liked some of the articles in the Liberator. She tells about Lord Ellenborough&apos;s work for the removal of &quot;all kinds of slavery&quot; in India. Sturge writes: &quot;We cannot help thinking the difficulty much greater for you, as there are so many powers to contend with and a blind prejudice to oppose especially that of colour, your very children have learned it as with their very growth, ...&quot; Sturge suggests raising a fund to help runaway slaves. She notes improvement in the condition of the English poor. Esther Sturge&apos;s brothers, Thomas, Samuel, and George have been active; one brother has been involved with the Manufacturers Relief Committee.</subfield>
